When the Ars Poetica was transferred by H. Stephanus and lambinus to its present place at the end of Horace’s works it seems to have been taken for granted that this was its true chronological position. Bentley so places it with very slight discussion. This. view has been maintained in this century by Kirchner, Ritter, ¹ Dillenburger and Orelli. Franke, on the other hand, leans to the earlier date, and this is the one which has been in most favour with recent critics. The arguments for it have been most fully stated by A.
